== Roast Potatoes ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve the @Salad Potatoes{350%g}(halved) and pop them on a
#baking tray{}. Drizzle over some @olive oil{} and sprinkle with the @dried oregano{1%tsp}
and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat, making sure they are in
a single layer. Roast on the top shelf of the oven until crispy on the outside and
soft in the middle, ~{30-35%minutes}, turn halfway through.

== Aubergine and Caper Salsa ==

Meanwhile, trim the @aubergine{1}(trimmed) then halve lengthways. Chop each half into
four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 2cm chunks. Halve the
@Premium Tomato Mix{250%g}(halved), peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated)
(or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the @Flat Leaf Parsley{1%bunch}(finely chopped,
stalks and all). Roughly chop the @Raisins{40%g}(roughly chopped). Zest and halve the
@lemon{1}(zested and halved). Squeeze half the lemon juice into a #bowl{}, set aside.
Chop the remaining lemon into wedges.

Pop the aubergine on a baking tray lined with #baking paper{}, drizzle with @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}.
Sprinkle on the @ground coriander{1%tsp} along with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch}. Toss until coated in oil, then roast on the middle shelf until golden
brown, ~{20-25%minutes}. We will add the fish to the tray when the aubergine has been
cooking for ~{10%minutes}.

Put the @pine nuts{15%g}, lemon zest, chopped raisins, @Panko Breadcrumbs{10%g},
@olive oil{1.5%tbsp} and half the parsley in a large bowl. Add a pinch of @salt{pinch}
and @pepper{pinch} and mix together until completely combined. Put the @Hake Fillet{2}
on a #plate{}, spoon the crumb on top of it. Press it down onto the fillet. When the
aubergine has been cooking for ~{10%minutes}, remove from the oven and carefully transfer
the fish to one end of baking tray using a #spatula{}.

Move the potatoes to the middle shelf, then bake the aubergine and fish on the top
shelf until the crumb is golden and the fish cooked, ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The
fish is cooked when opaque all the way though. Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of
@olive oil{for frying} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the tomatoes and a
pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}, then
add the garlic and @capers{15%g}, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}.

== Warm Dressing ==

While the tomatoes cook, add the @Olive Oil for the Dressing{1.5%tbsp} to the lemon
juice in the bowl. Add a pinch of @salt{pinch}, @pepper{pinch} and @sugar{pinch} and
the remaining parsley. When the tomatoes have softened and the aubergines are cooked,
add them both to the bowl and gently stir to combine.

Serve the hake with the roast potatoes and warmed aubergine and tomato salsa arranged
round the plate. Serve with lemon wedges and enjoy!